│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                             │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue: The assertion `TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == │
│ 1` fails because `TEPtr` (which is the first tree entry, index 0) has no    │
│ users (`UserTreeIndices.size() == 0`). This occurs when                     │
│ `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry` iterates over                         │
│ `ValueToGatherNodes.find(V)->second` and encounters a gather node that is   │
│ the root of the tree (the first entry). The root gather node may have zero  │
│ users because it's the topmost gather node. The assertion expects exactly   │
│ one user for a gather node, but the root gather node is an exception.       │
│                                                                             │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log: The log shows that the SLP vectorizer is trying   │
│ to vectorize a horizontal reduction. It builds a tree with several entries, │
│ including a gather node for `%cmp4.3`, `%tobool10.not`, `%cmp4.2`,          │
│ `%cmp4.1` (index 0). This gather node has no users because it's the root of │
│ the tree (the first entry). Later, when processing another gather node      │
│ (index 5), the code iterates over `ValueToGatherNodes` and includes the     │
│ root gather node (index 0) in the list of candidate entries. The assertion  │
│ triggers because the root gather node's `UserTreeIndices` is empty.         │
│                                                                             │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis: The function `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry`  │
│ assumes that any gather node found in `ValueToGatherNodes` (except `TE`     │
│ itself) must have exactly one user. However, the root gather node (the      │
│ first entry in `VectorizableTree`) may have zero users. The earlier         │
│ assertion at line 12793-12795 already acknowledges this exception:          │
│ `assert((TE->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 || TE ==                           │
│ VectorizableTree.front().get()) && "Expected only single user of the gather │
│ node.");`. The same exception should apply to `TEPtr` when `TEPtr` is the   │
│ root gather node.                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s): Modify the assertion at lines 12474-12475 to     │
│ allow `TEPtr` to be the root gather node (i.e., `TEPtr ==                   │
│ VectorizableTree.front().get()`). The fix is to change the assertion to:    │
│ ```cpp                                                                      │
│ assert((TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 || TEPtr ==                      │
│ VectorizableTree.front().get()) &&                                          │
│        "Expected only single user of a gather node.");                      │
│ ```                                                                         │
│ This matches the pattern used elsewhere in the same function (line          │
│ 12793-12795).                                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ 5. Conclusion: The fix ensures that the root gather node (which may have    │
│ zero users) does not trigger the assertion. This aligns with the existing   │
│ logic that already handles the root gather node as a special case. The      │
│ change should resolve the crash while preserving the intended behavior for  │
│ other gather nodes.                                                         │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                             │
